branchItem.description:
&lt;p&gt;
The ALD series, installed in a main airline, is designed to feed oil to various valves, air cylinders, air tools, etc. The use of the ALD series makes it possible to  centralize control of lubrication to end-line components. This lubrication feeding system, in which oil is in the form of micro mist, ensures stable lubrication over long, complex piping systems.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
Auto feed lube series ALF400 - 900 makes lubrication work unnecessary, thus significantly reducing the  amount of maintenance labor.  The problem of running out of oil is prevented because the oil is fed automatically.  
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
LMV series mixing valve is used with the LMU mist spray unit.  A needle valve is installed in the air passage of the mist generating mixing valve, hence it is possible to vary the size of the mist particles by regulating the  flowrate.  
&lt;/p&gt;
